The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
Archives
				 CPM leaders held hostage
 OUR BUREAU																								Oct. 12: CPM leaders of a Burdwan village were held hostage today after they tried to prevent a mob from looting a ration shop and its owners house.																								The mob pelted police with stones when they arrived at Chanduli village in Katwa, about 165km from Calcutta, around 11am. 																								A baton charge followed and tear gas shells were lobbed to rescue the leaders, including panchayat samiti chief Hari Narayan Samanta.																								The villagers had asked ration dealer Shibshankar Pal to pay Rs 6 lakh in a kan-garoo court after indicting him yesterday for selling foodgrain in the black market. They came to take the money today, but found the Pals mi-ssing and his shop closed, the police said.																								The villagers broke into the shop and his house and looted everything they could lay their hands on. 
